# GrowCold design system (web)

## Stack boundaries

- **`apps/web`** (Next.js + React + Tailwind): Use this design system — tokens and component classes from `apps/web/tailwind.config.ts`.
- **`apps/mobile`** (Expo + GlueStack): Do **not** apply Tailwind class names here; follow GlueStack theming, `specs/MOBILE_GLUESTACK_DESIGN_ALIGNMENT.md`, and `apps/mobile/src/theme/gluestack.config.ts` when changing tokens.

## Before changing UI

Read (or skim for relevance):

- `specs/DESIGN_SYSTEM_V1.md`
- `specs/DESIGN_SYSTEM_SUMMARY.md`
- `specs/COMPONENT_SPECS.md`
- `apps/web/tailwind.config.ts` (colors, `fontSize`, `@layer` plugins: `.btn-*`, `.card`, `.input-base`, etc.)

## Tokens and classes (web)

- Prefer **`primary`**, **`secondary`**, **`accent`**, **`success`**, **`warning`**, **`danger`**, **`neutral`**, and **`status.*`** over ad hoc palette utilities such as `slate`, `zinc`, or `blue` for product chrome and text.
- **Primary** is **Grab-inspired green** (`#00B14F` at `primary-500`). **Headings/body** use **Tuna** via `text-neutral-900` (`#363A45`). **Secondary buttons** are **neutral outline** (`.btn-secondary`); use **`Button` `variant="outline"`** for **green-outlined** secondary CTAs.
- Prefer documented component utilities: **`btn-primary`**, **`btn-secondary`**, **`btn-danger`**, **`btn-ghost`**, **`input-base`**, **`form-field`**, **`card`**, **`skeleton`**, **`help-text`**, **`error-text`**, **`badge-*`**, **`page-container`**, **`lot-grid`**, heading helpers **`.h1` / `.h2` / `.h3`**, and semantic text sizes **`text-h1`**, **`text-body-sm`**, **`text-label`**, etc.
- Use **`rounded-base`** (**12px**) for buttons and cards unless a spec calls for `rounded-lg` (16px) for large modules.
- **`Button` component** (`apps/web/src/components/ui/button.tsx`): Use variants **`default`** (primary green), **`secondary`** (gray outline), **`outline`** (green border), **`danger`**, **`ghost`**.

## Standard UI sizing (web — platform guidelines)

- **Touch height:** **`min-h-touch` = 44px** (Apple HIG–style minimum; `min-h-11` in utilities). This is the product default, not a separate “accessibility mode.”
- **Primary buttons & inputs:** **`py-2.5` `px-3.5`**, **min height 44px** via `.btn-base` / `.input-base` / `Button` variants.
- **Form inputs:** **`text-base` (16px)** on `<input>`, `<select>`, `<textarea>` so iOS does not zoom on focus; do not use smaller type on real inputs.
- **Between targets:** **≥8px** gap between adjacent tappable controls (industry / WCAG 2.2 spacing for pointer targets).
- **Secondary copy:** **12px+** for important chrome (`text-caption` / `text-label` as documented); do not go below without layout justification.

## Semantics & keyboard (non-negotiable)

- Form controls: **`<label htmlFor>`** paired with **`id`**; **`aria-invalid`**, **`aria-describedby`** for errors; do not use placeholder as the only label.
- Interactive controls: **focus-visible** affordance (visible focus ring or equivalent).
- Icon-only buttons: **`aria-label`**.

## What not to do

- Do not introduce one-off hex colors or default gray palettes for main surfaces when a token exists.
- Do not shrink body text below **16px** for primary reading content on mobile web without an explicit product exception.
